-- KDDI to Start Selling Smartphones Made by Sharp, Incoming President Says
-- B y   M a r i k o   Y a s u
-- 2010-11-26T00:33:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-26/kddi-to-start-selling-smartphones-made-by-sharp-incoming-president-says.html
KDDI Corp., Japan’s second-largest
mobile-phone company, will begin selling a new smartphone made
by Sharp Corp. starting today.  The company had placed an order for 600,000 units with
Sharp, KDDI’s incoming President Takashi Tanaka said in Tokyo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mariko Yasu in 東京 at 
